HEADWORD: meritocracy
<hw>meritocracy</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A form of social
system in which power goes to those with superior intellects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The belief that rulers should be chosen for their
superior abilities and not because of their wealth or birth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>meritocratic</ent>⟦br⟧
